16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 14-137, as
18 amended by Section 1, Chapter 78, O.S.L. 2024 (26 O.S. Supp. 2025,
19 Section 14-137), is amended to read as follows:
20 Section 14-137. As used in the Uniform Military and Overseas
21 Voters Act:
22 1. "Covered voter" means:
23 a. a uniformed-service voter or an overseas voter who is
24 registered to vote in this state,
Req. No. 15988 Page 1

1 b. a uniformed-service voter defined in subparagraph a of
2 paragraph 9 of this section, whose voting residence is
3 in this state and who otherwise satisfies this state's
4 voter eligibility requirements,
5 c. an overseas voter who, before leaving the United
6 States with an intent to return, was a bona fide
7 resident of Oklahoma and last eligible to vote in this
8 state and, except for a state residency requirement,
9 otherwise satisfies this state's voter eligibility
10 requirements, or
11 d. an overseas voter who, before leaving the United
12 States with an intent to return and was a bona fide
13 resident of Oklahoma, would have been last eligible to
14 vote in this state had the voter then been of voting
15 age and, except for a state residency requirement,
16 otherwise satisfies this state's voter eligibility
17 requirements, or
18 e. an overseas voter who was born outside the United
19 States, is not described in subparagraph c or d of
20 this paragraph, and, except for a state residency
21 requirement, otherwise satisfies this state's voter
22 eligibility requirements, if:
23 (1) the last place where a parent or legal guardian
24 of the voter was, or under the Uniform Military
