1 and Overseas Voters Act would have been, eligible
2 to vote before leaving the United States is
3 within this state, and
4 (2) the voter has not previously registered to vote
5 in any other state;
6 2. "Dependent" means an individual recognized as a dependent by
7 a uniformed service;
8 3. "Federal postcard application" means the application
9 prescribed under Section 101(b)(2) of the Uniformed and Overseas
10 Citizens Absentee Voting Act, 42 U.S.C. Section 1973ff(b)(2);
11 4. "Federal write-in absentee ballot" means the ballot
12 described in Section 103 of the Uniformed and Overseas Citizens
13 Absentee Voting Act, 42 U.S.C. Section 1973ff-2;
14 5. "Military-overseas ballot" means:
15 a. a federal write-in absentee ballot,
16 b. a ballot specifically prepared or distributed for use
17 by a covered voter in accordance with Section 14-136
18 et seq. of this title, or
19 c. a ballot cast by a covered voter in accordance with
20 the Uniform Military and Overseas Voters Act;
21 6. "Overseas voter" means a United States citizen who is
22 outside the United States;
23 7. "State" means a state of the United States, the District of
24 Columbia, Puerto Rico, the United States Virgin Islands, or any
Req. No. 15988 Page 3

1 terr itory or insular possession subject to the jurisdiction of the
2 United States;
3 8. "Uniformed service" means:
4 a. active and reserve components of the Army, Navy, Air
5 Force, Marine Corps, Space Force, or Coast Guard of
6 the United States,
7 b. the Merchant Marine, the commissioned corps of the
8 Public Health Service, or the commissioned corps of
9 the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration of
10 the United States, or
11 c. the National Guard and state militia;
12 9. "Uniformed-service voter" means an individual who is
13 qualified to vote and is:
14 a. a member of the active or reserve components of the
15 Army, Navy, Air Force, Marine Corps, Space Force, or
16 Coast Guard of the United States who is on active
17 duty,
18 b. a member of the Merchant Marine, the commissioned
19 corps of the Public Health Service, or the
20 commissioned corps of the National Oceanic and
21 Atmospheric Administration of the United States,
22 c. a member on activated status of the National Guard or
23 state militia, or
24
